<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="x_snc_nnemc0_funds_transaction_stages">
    <x_snc_nnemc0_funds_transaction_stages action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <fund_stage_description>A firm administrative reservation of funds based on solid procurement
directives, unaccepted customer orders, requisitions, authorizations to issue travel
orders, or equivalent instruments which authorize the recipient to create obligations
without further recourse to the official responsible for certifying the availability of funds. A
commitment is generally recorded when the comptroller signs the document to certify
that the funds are available and properly cited for the effort. Only warranted or
authorized personnel can legally obligate government funds. </fund_stage_description>
        <fund_stage_name>Commitment</fund_stage_name>
